[SN]TITLE[SN]
South Ayrshire Council agrees £9.4m of savings

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
South Ayrshire Council has agreed to make cuts totalling £9.4m in order to balance its budget for 2016/2017.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The authority approved £3.2m of savings as part of next year's budget, adding to the £6.2m previously approved.
The measures include a 5% price rise for school meals and sports and leisure centre costs and a reduction of 13 school assistant posts.
Council leader Bill McIntosh said it had been "the most difficult budget we've ever had to agree".
"We can no longer avoid making difficult choices and hard decisions - decisions which, in normal circumstances, we would not take," he said.
"However, we cannot live beyond our means and we need to do all we can to protect and sustain essential services - the ones that really matter in terms of life or limb - for the future."
